column1: it is a post about how it is to be a 'mother of boys' in the age of #metoo
i had started writing a new one until i re- discovered this one. '3 men and a lady - building better boys'

is a look at how we might present a more unified relationship between men and women in the future instead of the 'gender war' that is so often portrayed and how being a mum in a house full of boys is possibly never been more important.

column1: 305010;instagram;2018-10-09 08:22:05;FALSE;"it’s not only men. women narcissists can come in different forms: girlfriends
column5: friends...there is a roommate i lived with who
column7: was totally a narcissist. there was constant conflict
column8: control and condescending remarks. for example: i came home one day to find all of my bathroom toiletries (toothbrush
column9: proactiv treatments and hairbrush) on my nightstand in my bedroom. she told me that she doesn’t need to see all of my “acne shit” on our sink. another time i came home about 15 minutes later than i usually do at night and she waiting up for me asking how it could possibly have taken me 15 minutes longer and i held up my cvs bag and said
column11: i needed tampons...”. i was questioned up and down from the moment i clocked out
column12: took the shuttle and stopped at the store—and we didn’t even have plans! she was just pissed i wasn’t home “on time”. she would get mad at me for watching tv in the living room while she was in the kitchen with her sister
column13: telling me that i was interfering with her sister time. another time
column14: i started hanging out with another girl at work i became friends with
column15: and my roommate first tried telling me how bad she was for me
column16: then when it came time to move out because our lease ended and i was planning on getting a place with my new friend
column17: she tried getting my friend to get a place with her—even offering her a room for free at her parents’ house until they found a “better apartment”. you see
column18: all of these isolated incidents are subtle and don’t seem to be that big of a deal. but when you combine those and so many more
column19: you’re able to step back and say: holy shit. something isn’t normal. •

column4: these are things you learn with experiences. experiences that are horrific! growing up
column5: i lived in an apartment in hyderabad and my neighbor was a close friend. i would spend a lot of time at her house
column6: studying or just playing. every time my friend would go to the bathroom
column7: her father would pull me close and touch me inappropriately. let me give you a few details. he would first touch my hand… then move to my neck and finally
column8: rub my breasts. i was in class 10
column9: about 14-years-old. i didn’t have a mother to tell me how and when to wear a bra. i would just wear a tee shirt
column11: my body parts were slightly visible. back then
column12: i never realized he was doing something wrong. yes
column13: i was awkward. but he was my friend’s father. he was close to my family. so
column14: i kept quiet. he continued to do it and only after a year i understood that i should do something because it made me feel very uncomfortable. so i stopped visiting them. i thought i was done with episodes like that. i was so naive
column15: i didn’t know the world is filled with similar men who just want to get their hands on women. eve teasing
column16: awkward touches in public transport… what not! what bothered me the most about my neighbor was that he had two daughters
column17: one of them was my friend. i couldn’t even imagine how she spent all her life with him if he was doing similar things to her. even if he didn’t
column18: just the thought about sexually harassing another small girl when he has two daughters himself was disgusting...

a top trump campaign official requested proposals in 2016 from an israeli company to create fake online identities
column2: to use social media manipulation and to gather intelligence to help defeat republican primary race opponents and hillary clinton
column3: according to interviews and copies of the proposals.

column1: the trump campaign’s interest in the work began as russians were escalating their effort to aid donald j. trump. though the israeli company’s pitches were narrower than moscow’s interference campaign and appear unconnected
column2: the documents show that a senior trump aide saw the promise of a disruption effort to swing voters in mr. trump’s favor.

column3: sought one proposal to use bogus personas to target and sway 5
column4: 000 delegates to the 2016 republican national convention by attacking senator ted cruz of texas
column5: mr. trump’s main opponent at the time. another proposal describes opposition research and “complementary intelligence activities” about mrs. clinton and people close to her
column6: according to copies of the proposals obtained by the new york times and interviews with four people involved in creating the documents.  stay focused! don’t get discouraged

column2: i drew this the day my friend forced me to tell the school councillor who told the police about me being sexually assaulted. for me
column3: it was like she was saying “i’m doing this for you” while hanging me over the edge of a cliff. but
column4: that was just the fear. finally most of it is over and these just the court trial to go which will happen in a few months and everything is being fixed. i’ve been getting the help i’ve needed for years and the offender isn’t allowed to see me. this has all be so worth it and to anyone who is afraid to speak up
column5: please please please dm me and i can tell you how much better life is once you’ve told someone. things actually get sorted. #metoo #metoomovement #metoo❤️ #standup #letsendrape #letsendrapeculture #stoprape #endrape #endrapeculture #sexualassualt #assualt #itgetsbetter #ink #sketch #sketchbook;;en;#metoo

and there in the woods is where i should lie deceased
for 4 hours i was expecting to die

and this was all done as we were both sober

he decided that it was time to take me to

and develop stomach ulcers from the emotions i'm suppressin
i'm hoping this cry for help will ease my sufferin

column1: the metoo campaign has reached the malayalam movie industry. technical director tess joseph is the new one to join the #metoo campaign. she has raised allegations against malayalam actor and mla mukesh.

tess shared her negative experience with mukesh on twitter. she wrote that she was one of the crew members of the malayalam quiz show ‘kodeeswaran’ hosted by mukesh. she was then 20 years old. mukesh had allegedly called her multiple times and changed her room next to mukesh. it was her boss and trinamul congres leader derek o'brien who helped her leave the shooting spot by the next flight. tess thanked her boss for his kind gesture.
she also added that it took 19 years for her to reveal.
the post was captioned ‘took 19 years but here is my story.

column2: actor mukesh termed the allegations baseless and said he does not know who the person is.

column2: resilient and in total balance. my cycle is usually 28-30 days long

column2: #mcaday16 started off epic. i was a machine. wrote 600 words of my latest book (aiming for 600 words every morning before i do anything) followed by a 1800 word blog post all about creating a culture of consent (link in stories!) and then recorded this week’s youtube video
column3: all about anger. totally cranking. feeling so clearheaded and driven. and then. i was talking on the phone
column4: playing with a bit of ponga palm when the bark flew into my eye. the pain was so extreme (more intense than childbirth no jokes) that i spent the afternoon at the docs and now can’t open my swollen eye. the pain is still so strong that i’m in bed listening to podcasts 😔 argh. i’m so keen to answer the question “why chart your menstrual cycle?” but i’m on major pain killers and i feel a bit out of it. booo. feeling so grateful that i was able to record this week’s video with both eyes working! and hoping the pain is gone by tomorrow. so cool to read so many people’s instagram menstrual cycle tracking 😍❤️😍 it makes me feel so connected to this woven womb web ☺️ ❤️❤️ ps do read my latest blog post - lots of important ideas about how we can dismantle rape culture

column1: 305109;instagram;2018-10-09 06:28:50;FALSE;"what? what's wrong? is it my skin? that has got a little mischievous and wants to peep out a bit? the part of skin that is otherwise expected to be concealed behind a piece of cloth?
oh yes! let me guess because you are not used to it.
nobody ever told you that a woman has only her right over her body and not the men in the house who with furious eyes order her to put dupatta back on the shoulder
column2: and cover up while she is dripping wet in sweat due to working all day long for your comfort.

column1: year by year you had managed to figure out and hardwire it in your brain that women are supposed to cover up her significant portions of skin even if she is uncomfortable while doing that.

she will always have to put her gaze down in shame while pulling her fallen dupatta back onto it's position so that it doesn't entice the male members of your family. those male members whom you have ironically always seen sitting in their boxers and vests.
being habitual of noticing certain kind of behaviour year by year
column2: you have started believing that this is how it works.

column1: now an eighteen year old you along with your mother
column2: orders their sister (daughter)  to have the same ""etiquette"" around men of the house by making her nearly believing that ""good girls never expose"". you have snatched all her rights to even choose her clothes for herself fearing your own kind. yet again you made yourself entitled to take away all her rights to choose the kind of beautiful she wants to be
column3: without even knowing the hidden subtleness of patriarchy you have just fallen victim to.

column2: it's not about the western or traditional outfits. since a 6 inch gap between  blouse and a saree doesn't nullify a 3 inch gap between a crop top and jeans. let her chose how much or how little she wants to look beautiful. let her be the owner of her own choices.

column1: 305151;instagram;2018-10-09 05:55:44;FALSE;"a very rare non-slimming world related post from me this morning but an important one to share! .........
.......... a collaboration between more than 60 charities across the uk
column2: baby loss awareness week is held from 9 to 15 october to raise awareness about the key issues affecting those who have experienced pregnancy loss or baby death in the uk..............
my husband and i tried for a baby for 2 years before i found out i was expecting in october 2013
column3: sadly i suffered a miscarriage soon after at 6 weeks. two months later on new year days 2014
column4: we found we were expecting again and although initially nervous

column4: better shut your mouth. women are meant to lift each other and give love and support to each other.

column1: so next time if someone says “me too” either trust her or reserve your opinion. bless you all. xx

column1: 305186;instagram;2018-10-09 05:25:18;FALSE;"günaydııın ☀️ bayan yanı ekim sayısı bayilerde. bu ay cinsel tacizi yazdım
her yeni akademik dönem başlangıcında üniversiteler alanlarında tanınmış
column2: hatta ünü kendi alanı dışına taşmış birini öğretim yılının “ilk dersini” vermeye çağırırlar ve bu konu da genelde o anki bakış açısını çerçeveleyip üniversitenin de duruşunun altını çizer.  bu ilk konuşma bana düşseydi bu yıl kesinlike dünyayı çalkalayan ama bir türlü türkiye’de yeterince ilgi ve yasal işlem göremeyen cinsel taciz ile ilgili konuşurdum.  koskoca akademik yılı cinsel taciz ile mi çerçeveleyeceksin demeyin
column3: cinsel taciz aslında bir toplumsal cinsiyet eşitsizliği sorunu olduğu için özünde bir adalet
column4: özgürlük ve eşitlik problemidir. cinsel taciz güç dengesizliklerinden doğar ve toplumda genelde erkeklerin fail

column2: oregon's senator @senjeffmerkley stood on the senate floor and read every single one of the sexual assault accounts from calls he received. it was the early morning hours. the chamber was empty. but what is spoken from the senate floor must be recorded and he wanted to make sure they were accounted for. i'm proud of this man and have felt very secure under his tending and leadership for my state. it's things like this that don't make big news that are the things that matter. #liberal #jeffmerkley #goodman #oregon #politics #believesurvivors #believeallsurvivors #sexualassault #ally #senator #metoo #hero #survivor #survivors #support #supportsurvivors;;en;#Liberal

column1: 305192;instagram;2018-10-09 05:29:35;FALSE;"the truth is we all need to be held.

column2: affection and approval from one another.

column1: the place and space to be truly seen
column2: heard and express our sacred truths.

column1: there has been a lot of talk lately around the #metoo movement. a lot of discussion around the pain that men have caused women. i hear
column2: see and value this truth that is being shared and i strongly believe it’s necessary in order to all of us to heal.

column1: there is however a shadow side i believe isn’t being brought to life. what about what has happened to our men? what pressures
column2: pain and misguidance have they gone through that has led them down the path of fear

column1: how have we raised our boys to become men? how have we allowed ourselves to be treated? how can we all take responsibility and begin doing the #innerwork so that we can all truly heal the #masculine and #feminine within?
as a women leading men’s circles it’s been an incredible honor to be able to hold space for men to feel they can finally be seen
column3: held and supported by one another. i am finally able to understand what for so long we’ve prevented our men from sharing.

column1: this picture was captured at the end of the men’s gathering at @om.rising  and it truly represents the masculine within us all (male
column2: female or anywhere in between) coming back together to support
column3: share and embrace all aspects of ourself.

column1: 305245;instagram;2018-10-09 05:01:04;FALSE;"असली ज़िन्दगी के #heroes !!! आज के दौर में जहाँ हम आए दिन महिलाओं के साथ होने वाली किसी ना किसी दुःखद अप्रिय घटना की ख़बरें पढ़ते-सुनते रहते हैं और सोशल मीडिया पर #metoo ट्रेंड करता रहता है
column2: ऐसे वक़्त में ऐसी ख़बरें सुखद हवा के झोंके सी लगती हैं !

column1: मुम्बई की 25 वर्षीय मंताशा शेख़ का एक ट्वीट इन दिनों बेहद चर्चा में है जिसमें उन्होंने अपना अनुभव साझा करते हुए बताया है की 4 अक्टूबर 2018 की रात उन्होंने साकीनाका से अपने घर के लिए बस पकड़ी और घर के करीबी आख़िरी बस स्टैंड पर पहुँचते-पहुँचते उन्हें रात के डेढ़ बज गए थे और बस स्टैंड और आसपास का इलाका पूरी तरह सूनसान था | स्तिथि को भांपते हुए बस के ड्राइवर ने उनसे पूछा की क्या उन्हें कोई लेने आ रहा है ? मंताशा के इंकार करने पर यह समझते हुए की इतनी देर रात सूनसान बस स्टैण्ड पर उसे अकेले ऑटो का इंतज़ार करना पड़ेगा बेस्ट बस के ड्राइवर प्रशान्त मायेकर और कंडक्टर राज दिनकर ने बस साइड में लगा दी और तब तक रुके रहे जब तक की उसे ऑटो नहीं मिल गया |
मंताशा का यह ट्वीट दो हज़ार से भी ज़्यादा बार #retweet किया जा चुका है
column2: वे कहती हैं की अगर उस रात वे दोनों वहाँ नहीं रुकते तो यह कहानी कुछ और भी हो सकती थी | सोशल मीडिया पर इस ख़बर के वायरल होने के बाद बस ड्राइवर प्रशान्त और कंडक्टर राज से कई अख़बार वालों ने सम्पर्क किया जिस पर उनका कहना था की हमारी बस से ज़्यादातर आख़िर में उतरने वाली महिलाएँ और बुज़ुर्ग ही होते हैं और उनकी सुरक्षा हमारी ज़िम्मेदारी है ख़ास कर जब इतनी देर रात हो जाए और कोई इतना सूनसान स्टॉप हो |

column1: अक्सर जब ऐसी किन्हीं घटनाओं के लिए उल्टा पीड़िता को ही कपड़ों या इतनी रात गए बाहर होने का कह कर दोषी ठहरा दिया जाता है यह वाकया ज़िन्दा उदाहरण है की वो सब बेवजह की फ़िजूल बातें नहीं पर नेकी और आदमी की नियत ही सबसे अधिक मायने रखती है और असली मर्दानगी इसे ही कहते हैं !
असली ज़िन्दगी के इन दोनों असली नायकों #prashantmayekar और #rajdinkar को हमारा सलाम

column3: ज़िन्दगी और ज़िन्दादिली की इस positive ख़बर को #share ज़रूर करते चलें !

column1: जय हिन्द | वन्दे मातरम✊🏼🇮🇳️                  heroes🤘🏼";असली ज़िन्दगी के ! ! ! आज के दौर में जहाँ हम आए दिन महिलाओं के साथ होने वाली किसी ना किसी दुःखद अप्रिय घटना की ख़बरें पढ़ते-सुनते रहते हैं और सोशल मीडिया पर ट्रेंड करता रहता है
column2: ऐसे वक़्त में ऐसी ख़बरें सुखद हवा के झोंके सी लगती हैं ! मुम्बई की 25 वर्षीय मंताशा शेख़ का एक ट्वीट इन दिनों बेहद चर्चा में है जिसमें उन्होंने अपना अनुभव साझा करते हुए बताया है की 4 अक्टूबर 2018 की रात उन्होंने साकीनाका से अपने घर के लिए बस पकड़ी और घर के करीबी आख़िरी बस स्टैंड पर पहुँचते-पहुँचते उन्हें रात के डेढ़ बज गए थे और बस स्टैंड और आसपास का इलाका पूरी तरह सूनसान था | स्तिथि को भांपते हुए बस के ड्राइवर ने उनसे पूछा की क्या उन्हें कोई लेने आ रहा है ? मंताशा के इंकार करने पर यह समझते हुए की इतनी देर रात सूनसान बस स्टैण्ड पर उसे अकेले ऑटो का इंतज़ार करना पड़ेगा बेस्ट बस के ड्राइवर प्रशान्त मायेकर और कंडक्टर राज दिनकर ने बस साइड में लगा दी और तब तक रुके रहे जब तक की उसे ऑटो नहीं मिल गया | मंताशा का यह ट्वीट दो हज़ार से भी ज़्यादा बार किया जा चुका है
column3: वे कहती हैं की अगर उस रात वे दोनों वहाँ नहीं रुकते तो यह कहानी कुछ और भी हो सकती थी | सोशल मीडिया पर इस ख़बर के वायरल होने के बाद बस ड्राइवर प्रशान्त और कंडक्टर राज से कई अख़बार वालों ने सम्पर्क किया जिस पर उनका कहना था की हमारी बस से ज़्यादातर आख़िर में उतरने वाली महिलाएँ और बुज़ुर्ग ही होते हैं और उनकी सुरक्षा हमारी ज़िम्मेदारी है ख़ास कर जब इतनी देर रात हो जाए और कोई इतना सूनसान स्टॉप हो | अक्सर जब ऐसी किन्हीं घटनाओं के लिए उल्टा पीड़िता को ही कपड़ों या इतनी रात गए बाहर होने का कह कर दोषी ठहरा दिया जाता है यह वाकया ज़िन्दा उदाहरण है की वो सब बेवजह की फ़िजूल बातें नहीं पर नेकी और आदमी की नियत ही सबसे अधिक मायने रखती है और असली मर्दानगी इसे ही कहते हैं ! असली ज़िन्दगी के इन दोनों असली नायकों और को हमारा सलाम

column1: if you are a survivor please
column2: please take care of your mental health and ask for the help that you need. i strongly recommend therapy. it’s saved my life more than once. do your best to find a support system and remember that self care is essential. most importantly know that it is not your fault and you are not alone.

column3: step back and listen to survivors. stop blaming and berating the women and men who come forward for not reporting assaults sooner. assaults are incredibly scary and traumatic events. everyone has their reasons for not reporting. it’s so easy to sit back and say what you would do if you were in that situation. when you’re actually there it’s so much more complex. let’s all be kind to one another because there’s enough ugliness in the world as it is. don’t be part of the problem.";;en;#metoo;;;;;0;;_rachel_green._;Rachel Green;;0;False;1;0;0;31;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/2d7cc9624c954ffeb1aa120a23942630/5D11C61B/t51.2885-15/e35/42355741_336705473750582_704848180427441255_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;"#metoo not ashamed. not alone.

column1: october has become a special month to me because it is domestic violence awareness month. i’ve had a lot on my mind lately honestly... last month was the most depressed i’ve been in a long time (health related). i haven’t been able to think clearly or express in writing how i’m feeling
column2: which is usually very easy for me to do. i thought i’ve healed a lot
column3: i’m better... but last month really made me realize that i still have a whole lot of healing left to do... a lot of sadness and anger still left in me. i still have a ways to go even though 3 years has passed since i escaped from my abuser in asahikawa. being on facebook lately doesn’t help the confusion i feel towards what is going on in america. seeing trevor noah’s and my friend nadia’s content though has helped me understand what i’m feeling. i have a story that i won’t ever forget and one day i’ll tell my children how i escaped from a monster and found my knight in skiing armor afterwards.

column1: i got off the phone tonight with my dad and told him why i didn’t go to the cops during that time in japan. in my head all i was thinking was how can i get out... when... all i want to do is leave as peacefully as possible. also being a gaijin probably didn’t help. i just wanted out. a couple guys who knew what happened to me said “this is just classic japanese man”..... i remember feeling appalled at that sentence and whole heartedly angry for people to dismiss being attacked as just a “classic” act.  i think that’s the first time i’ve told a family member why i never told the cops. in hindsight
column2: that’s pretty fucked up... i couldn’t tell authorities and so many others are in the same boat. there’s a lot more to my story
column3: maybe i’ll share more one day. 💜#whyididntreport #metoo";;en;#metoo;;;;;0;;danidphoto;DANI - 山ild;;0;False;11;0;0;57;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/f011ad556a8a027502c6d7401dba4816/5D1C5170/t51.2885-15/e35/42728552_251993692180918_863330420693593944_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;"so... it’s october.

column2: october 11 will be my first public speaking about the genesis of my #metoo series and what my ultimate intention for this particular body of work  is.the st. helena soroptimists have invited me to give an introduction to my #metoo art which will be exhibited in conjunction with the soroptimist sponsored human trafficking awareness forum on november 8.

column1: it is clear to me that my ultimate purpose and intention for this body of work is healing
column2: wholeness and transformation.  my #metoo art marks the first step towards that end.  it holds the emotional
column3: psychic truth of my experience of childhood sexual abuse.abuse that my family denied.abuse that left me isolated and alone
column5: shamed and hurting from age three. abuse that left me silenced
column7: terrified and determined to protect myself as the adults would not.

column1: step one is telling the truth. standing up and facing down the forces to stay silent
the forces that demand we keep the boat steady
column2: the water of everyone else’s feelings even and undisturbed.currently there is a tsunami of truth telling from women.i’m honored to be a drop in this huge ocean.

column2: as i post the subsequent steps necessary to reclaim our wholeness

column1: 305323;instagram;2018-10-09 03:26:53;FALSE;"i decided to take a before video for this 8 week program i’ve committed to because i want to really appreciate whatever transformation my body takes and it can be hard to catch those in pictures.
confession...i was nervous of what i’d see watching the raw video back. no posing
column3: me moving around versus posing in a way that’s flattering. showing my booty which you’ll notice i’ve never done because that’s the part of my body i feel like i’m constantly working on.

column2: i didn’t start this program cold turkey. i’ve been pretty consistent with 4-5 workouts each week but not following a specific program (summer got a little crazy without much structure). following the most drawn out miscarriage of all time
column3: focusing on what my body can do this summer was healing mentally

column1: before you roll your eyes all the way in the back of your head remember we all have insecurities and we all have goals. as long as the goals are healthy
column2: realistic and our identity is not tied to our figures it’s perfectly fine to prove to ourselves just how fearfully and wonderfully made we are.

column1: when i’ve hit the end (or maybe halfway?) point of my program i’ll share the *before* photo with an *after* but for now

column1: 305324;instagram;2018-10-09 03:28:50;FALSE;"i’ve been reluctant to tell this story because i didn’t want to start a heavy debate but i’ve decided to share it because i think this is really important.

i was on a boat party this weekend and i witnessed two girls dancing and get physically too close to this guy just to get his attention. i continued to watch for a while to gauge how he was going to take it and whether he was even interested but it was clear he wanted nothing to do with them. i thought that eventually these girls would just get the message and stop dancing so close to him but they kept persisting and wouldn’t leave him alone. i didn’t know how the guy was feeling but watching this was even causing me to get irritate by it. it wasn’t until i saw one of the girls really trying to rub her butt in to the guy’s front part of his body that i got infuriated by it and i had had enough. i immediately thought that even if you are a man or woman
column2: no one should be getting harassed! so with this strong belief and overwhelming outrage i couldn’t stand to let this behavior go on and i just intervened (which is something i don’t normally do) to ask if this guy was okay. he said he was fine but i continued loudly to say and explain that i felt bad for him because i felt these girls were harassing him. he seemed to find the whole thing amusing and the girls weren’t too happy with me for calling them out on it. the girls  immediately kept a respectable distance away from the guy and stopped harassing him.

column1: i’m telling this story because i firmly believe that if women want and are demanding to not be harassed by men then it is not okay for them to harass men and we need to hold ourselves to a better standard and example for men to follow. and men; just because it’s a girl and you don’t feel physically threatened
column2: it is not amusing or okay for a woman to physically harass you.

column1: there should be no double standard when it comes to physical harassment. it is unacceptable
column2: bad and wrong on all accounts.

column1: the metoo movement doesn’t just apply to women
column2: it applies to all people! and absolutely no one should be getting harassed!

column2: no one should be getting harassed! so with this strong belief and overwhelming outrage i couldn’t stand to let this behavior go on and i just intervened (which is something i don’t normally do) to ask if this guy was okay. he said he was fine but i continued loudly to say and explain that i felt bad for him because i felt these girls were harassing him. he seemed to find the whole thing amusing and the girls weren’t too happy with me for calling them out on it. the girls  immediately kept a respectable distance away from the guy and stopped harassing him.

column1: i’m telling this story because i firmly believe that if women want and are demanding to not be harassed by men then it is not okay for them to harass men and we need to hold ourselves to a better standard and example for men to follow. and men; just because it’s a girl and you don’t feel physically threatened
column2: it is not amusing or okay for a woman to physically harass you.

column1: there should be no double standard when it comes to physical harassment. it is unacceptable
column2: bad and wrong on all accounts.

column1: the metoo movement doesn’t just apply to women
column2: it applies to all people! and absolutely no one should be getting harassed!

column1: 305441;instagram;2018-10-09 02:10:27;FALSE;"i haven’t felt like posting pretty photos this past week. it feels trivial when so much is going on in the world. and the emotions i have felt this week as a woman
column2: brought me back to this painting i did in college. i titled this painting “a woman’s worth” ironically because i was disgusted at where i saw the value being placed on women. 20 years ago i was asking some of these questions:

column6: our strength being valued as much as our sex appeal?

column1: why were we only seen on the surface and not seen as an equal?
why couldn’t the values that form us as women be even more important than the form of our bodies?
why did people want to look at us more than they wanted to hear from us?
why were the rules that applied to the guys not the same ones for us?
almost 20 years later and last week triggered so many feelings. i felt the rush of all those emotions all over again. i have at other times since the creation of this painting
column2: felt enraged on behalf of women. but last week was such a hard realization that not enough has changed. not nearly enough.

column1: sad to say that if i were to paint another piece today
column2: it would express a similar pain and disappointment in the current way women are valued and the inequality we face. it would be angry and smeared with frustrated tears and the color of heartbreak. but...my hope that i must cling to
column3: is that in 20 years when i look back at the painting of today
column4: i will see a sad memory of a time that no longer exists. and i look forward to being inspired in 20 years to paint something beautiful - full of a vibrant representation of where we are all thriving together now as equals.

en colombia se está dando un movimiento de activismo bien interesante en esta oportunidad de trata de mutantv una cuenta que abre la primera ""conversación digital"" para debatir sobre la violencia sexual en este país... me tiene atrapada la precisión con la que hablan el tema y la forma de invitar a la población general a hablar del tema... esto es un acto admirable y por ello hago eco de esta cuenta. .
porque tenemos que hablar de esto y tenemos que hablar de esto ya

column1: 305468;instagram;2018-10-09 01:20:37;FALSE;"hi! my name is gina king and i wanted to introduce you to the woman behind my worth girl and the one writing these posts. i’m a real woman that has experienced the most amazing blessings and i’ve also experienced traumas that god only truly knows..
i started my worth girl after my heart had been broken. at the time it felt like it was never going to recover. we’ve all been there- heartbreak
column4: sadness all parts of life—and what i have learned is that during these times is that beauty
column11: and humbleness comes out with a certain fire that can’t be extinguished. .

column1: i have gone through my own transformation about understanding and believing  my worth.  i am enough by simply being me. .

column2: (before my heartbreak) my story is much like many other woman- our traumas can flashback in our heads so visibly it is like it is happening all over again. i have experienced many different types of traumas in my life that are being talked about in the news on a daily basis.  and i want to tell you
column3: that you are not alone. your life and story matters. .

column1: i decided i wanted to empower as many girls and women as possible so that they wouldn’t live the way i used to. i want to teach you all about self-love and your self-worth. it has been an epic journey with many mountains and valleys and plateaus. i wouldn’t trade my journey because it led me here today
column5: teach self-love to all of you. you are all amazing

column1: 305470;instagram;2018-10-09 01:28:14;FALSE;"almost every day this is a cause for celebration
the more i talk about this the more *inconvenient* i feel
i haven’t posted one of these ~pure raging~ posts in a while but here’s why i’m going for it now:
- a (female) taxi driver denounced my move because canada is as shit as britain
column2: according to her and shitey far-right ezra levant (fuck tommy pedo robinson btw) who she recommended i listen to;

column1: - a whole bus full of us was faced with an enoch-powell-venomous-shite-spouting-self-described-neo-nazi who i had a face off with;
- i bumped into a cis-het drug dealing scumbag i vaguely know
column3: who told me they’d blocked me on social media bc i hate men. i don’t hate men
column4: i’m increasingly *afraid of* men. after gaining my trust
column6: by telling me they’d murder rapists for moral reasons (scary but the conversation had layers) - i was invited to his for a joint which ended in a conversation about his hatred of feminists and him trying to get me to kiss him even though i said no. when i told him i was scared and latered the fuck out i avoided the taxi he called for me because i know he can call some sketchy people and have them be there just as quick as a cab;

column1: - the predators at the top of the pile in basically every hierarchy (not least governments

column5: especially recently. this combined with the most recent extreme homophobia towards a femme (white) gay boy - when i confronted the wankers (3 men) being aggro af they said they were being racist. i literally had to tell them they were being homophobic and explain the difference.

column1: 305480;instagram;2018-10-09 01:44:31;FALSE;"are you aware of those that are tokens around you?

i took this picture at the national portraiture gallery when i recently visited it in dc. it is the four female supreme court justices. i wondered about how tokenism has shown up in their lives. “the truth is that most institutional change often begins with tokenism. it may even be a step in the right direction. but if you get comfortable with it
column2: there will never be true change. tokenism may be a good door opener
column3: but we must make sure to burst that door wide open. never be satisfied with mere tokenism. the full expression of our humanity requires genuine representation across the board. equity is the proper response to tokenism.” http://www.coachiyabo.com/possibilities-from-tokenism-to-community/

column1: 305496;instagram;2018-10-09 01:55:08;FALSE;i woke up today thinking about anger. about how until recently
column2: i’ve never had a good relationship with it. when i was a girl
column3: i was taught that to be angry was to be wrong. to be angry was to be unladylike. to be angry was to question authority. then my abuse happened. and happened. and happened. and i did not know how to be angry about it. i knew how to be sad. i knew how to be confused. but that was all. i spent more than a decade sad and confused
column4: with my anger buried deep within me because i did not want it. i did not like what i thought it made me. it was not until just a few years ago
column5: i found a therapy group for childhood survivors and i learned to embrace my anger
column7: to use my anger- for myself
column8: and for other survivors. as women
column9: we are often told that our anger is not attractive
column11: that our anger makes us less than. men of color are constantly told that their anger is dangerous. all of this is false. my anger is my shield. my anger is my sword. i am using my anger to start a community of survivors who will not be silenced. my anger is my engine. your anger can be yours. ✨ #survivor #metoo #anger #poetry;;en;#survivor

column1: 305508;instagram;2018-10-09 01:21:50;FALSE;"for the five people who follow me on here
column3: please know that there are countless reasons why cases of sexual assault go unspoken
column4: and our response can be a part of the reason why. too many lives are being wrecked by this for us to be quiet.

column1: it’s humiliating putting your dirtiest moments on public display
column4: or ask why you didn’t say something sooner. when you share something traumatic
column5: the last thing you want are questions regarding where you were and what you were wearing
column6: as if to find out if it was your fault. odds are
column7: you’ve already unfairly blamed yourself. you don’t need others to do the same.

column1: some people are afraid of their family reacting too strongly when they find out. on one end
column2: there’s the fear that their parents will physically harm or even kill the rapist. on the other
column3: there’s the fear that their parents will blame them for hanging around the wrong people or for not responding firmly enough.

column1: some people need to continue seeing the people who assaulted or harass them. they may work with them
column4: or be romantically involved with them. reporting sexual assault brings a social change that many people don’t think that they have the strength for.

column2: anyone reporting sexual assault knows that unless measures are taken during or immediately after the assault
column3: they likely don’t have any concrete evidence that it happened. people share their worst moments knowing that it’s going to end up as their word against their abuser. does a parent trust their child claiming abuse over their partner? does a country trust an everyday woman’s testimony or a governor? it can feel like picking a losing fight that will result in the survivor permanently defined as the person who cried rape.

column1: and unless their abuser is thrown in jail

column2: investigate as needed when someone reports their sexual assault
column3: but take time to listen and understand why reporting a traumatic event is tricky for some
column4: and all but impossible for others.

column3: please know that there are countless reasons why cases of sexual assault go unspoken

column1: it’s humiliating putting your dirtiest moments on public display
column4: or ask why you didn’t say something sooner. when you share something traumatic
column5: the last thing you want are questions regarding where you were and what you were wearing
column6: as if to find out if it was your fault. odds are
column7: you’ve already unfairly blamed yourself. you don’t need others to do the same.

column1: some people are afraid of their family reacting too strongly when they find out. on one end
column2: there’s the fear that their parents will physically harm or even kill the rapist. on the other
column3: there’s the fear that their parents will blame them for hanging around the wrong people or for not responding firmly enough.

column1: some people need to continue seeing the people who assaulted or harass them. they may work with them
column4: or be romantically involved with them. reporting sexual assault brings a social change that many people don’t think that they have the strength for.

column2: anyone reporting sexual assault knows that unless measures are taken during or immediately after the assault
column3: they likely don’t have any concrete evidence that it happened. people share their worst moments knowing that it’s going to end up as their word against their abuser. does a parent trust their child claiming abuse over their partner? does a country trust an everyday woman’s testimony or a governor? it can feel like picking a losing fight that will result in the survivor permanently defined as the person who cried rape.

column1: and unless their abuser is thrown in jail

column2: investigate as needed when someone reports their sexual assault
column3: but take time to listen and understand why reporting a traumatic event is tricky for some
column4: and all but impossible for others.

column1: 305522;instagram;2018-10-09 01:27:10;FALSE;"🌿meditation moment: gratitude for the freedoms we have right now in canada. gratitude for my family and for safe spaces and the gama studio. i have been sitting with the uneasy feeling that freedoms we take for granted can be revoked in a heartbeat and a vote.

🌿my heart goes out to those affected by sexual violence and the women and men who are victimized now and have been so traumatized in past. it has also been my experience that some men seem to feel that i
column3: am open season prey. it is not right.

column2: two emails crossed my inbox. one was from a young mom asking for help... my intuition telling me the situation was not safe.😪 the other from a married guy from my past asking for sex. 😳um
column3: no. what is the lie that has been festering in a man's mind that they should feel they have the right to betray the dignity of another person?

column1: ____ ❤there is healing that needs to happen for men and women both. emotional and physical pain can be passed on through generations as dis-ease
column2: as discord in the energy field
column3: the structure of the dna and the behavioural patterns of natural selection
column4: as well as societal ""norms."" the norms need a shake-up!

column1: 🙏beliefs need to be questioned and looked at objectively
column2: not with blame and hatred or self-flagellation but with compassion. the focus must  shift to a better and hope-full future in order to create it the way we want to see the future unfold for ourselves.

column1: 🌈looking ahead... watch for trauma-sensitive classes mondays and cacao ceremonies with music for reconnecting with the healing power within you. neither sexual betrayal nor violence should ever happen
column2: but it does and it is very important to be in community to deal with it. you are not alone. 🎶🎵🎼🙏 ____

column1: 305528;instagram;2018-10-09 01:30:39;FALSE;"✨the healing power of sharing your story✨
i recently spoke to a client whose story of sexual trauma i didn’t know
column2: from the initial rape that was her first sexual encounter to a sexual assault a few years later that left deep scars.

column1: she had compartmentalized her trauma to keep herself from having to feel the pain fully and in a way
column2: didn’t think it was something she needed to address. she wasn’t denying it happened
column3: she just didn’t bring it up and hadn’t ever spoken someone about it.

column1: being on a path of spiritual awakening
column2: inner work and healing for over twenty years now
column3: i can say without a doubt that life has a way of bringing your attention to aspects within you that still need your love.

column1: if you don’t heal from what hurt you
column2: that hurt will carry into your future like the current of a river running underground
column4: but it is there. unprocessed trauma or pain from your past creates change you didn’t choose. finding the courage to face your past and start a path of healing creates change you do choose.

column1: an unprocessed past shows up in ways we mostly are not aware of…such as in the subtle
column2: yet destructive inner voices that tell you aren’t good enough or the deep shame from believing the lie that you are “dirty” or damaged goods.

column1: it also shows up in the relationships we attract and the unhealthy patterns that emerge within those relationships.

column2: she knew it was time to face her past and bravely go into her trauma to finally heal. through the inner work and healing she has already done
column3: she now has a foundation of practices and tools she can draw from
column4: and support from myself and others to navigate the deep waters of processing trauma.

column1: her first step in healing was to share her story with people she could trust. she’s used her tools— witnessing her thoughts
column5: to cry and be comforted by people who love her.

column1: and all women who stand up and speak out.
and check out this inspiring video from @gracieandrachel!
link to full video in bio.

column4: an eager anticipation woke us up in our brooklyn loft unusually early. with our hearts racing
column5: we tuned into the hearings of dr. christine blasey ford and judge brett kavanaugh.

column1: amidst dr. ford’s emotionally brave testimony
column3: and an amalgamation of statements from an assembly of both incredibly compassionate and unbelievably ruthless senators
column4: we made a new song. and it was for her.

column2: we began putting a video together to more fully capture the inspiration behind this song. we wanted to point to women
column3: from a range of walks of life
column4: women who have taken a stance when it wasn’t necessarily easy to do so. our goal was to highlight the courage it takes to call something out loud and to stand up tall when the odds may not be in our favor.

column1: the women in this piece are just a few among many who inspire us to continue to use our voices and demand to be heard. the conclusory chorus lyric “never look back again” doesn’t imply we shouldn’t look back on the women who have taught us how to lead the way — we most absolutely should — but that we should always move bravely into the future. we hope with our song to thank the women who have empowered us so selflessly and perhaps to inspire those still searching to find their strengths.
see the full video for “her” now! link in bio.

column8: were created behind closed doors; they were written in human blood by our nation’s forefathers that still offer up whitehouse seats to rapists
column11: and racist men. it is my job to create opportunities that empower individuals to use what lies within them. and if they are unable to find that voice

column1: 305580;instagram;2018-10-09 00:26:33;FALSE;"i crave the wild. the abandon. the passion that arches my back and turns my hands into clenched fists. i crave raw
column2: unfiltered life. the unknown. trees naked and twisted into each other. skies soaring towards darkness. cliffs awash with raucous and unruly seabirds. the ocean raw and beating and abrasive spewing water and life and eternity into my midst. but i’m left with this. this as my viewscape. black fences. manicured lawn. manicured lake. manicured wildlife. manicured children. life manicured beyond recognition. regulated and overruled. life in suburbia. with expectations and commitments and playdates. play ie childhood fit in between the hours of 10 to 12. conversations without saying anything. anything that matters. not letting the facade slip. the truth seep past our tongue. seep past our manicured teeth. hiding my non manicured fingers. oh so avant-garde. my eternal rebellion. when did we all agree to a manicured life? that 2.5 kids
column4: 2 cars and a dog equal a life? that living to pay the bills for things we don’t need in a world that isn’t real is enough? that it doesn’t make our soul scream out loud? that it doesn’t betray our very existence? i was born for passion and abandon and the wild. and yet i hold my own pillow over my mouth to muffle my screams.

305599;instagram;2018-10-09 00:34:13;FALSE;“i am a fiercely independent person and i am no one’s pawn.” - dr. christine blasey ford ❂
sometimes i am at a loss for words over how a majority of our elected officials view us. the regressive steps that were taken by our federal government last week hurt my feminist soul. as a woman
column2: i worry my country does not have my back. as a citizen
column3: i doubt the credibility of our legal system. as a human being
column4: i fear the leading people do not care about anyone but themselves and their power. but with the devastating actions taken last week
column5: i witnessed thousands of women and men joining together in support. protests were had
column6: voices were raised! a platform on which survivors can come forward and demand justice is raising taller and taller. our government may have let us down last week
column7: but that does not mean our fight is over. midterm elections are just around the corner
column8: and the deadline to register is fast approaching. it is never too late to invoke change. it is becoming more and more apparent (with our razor thin voting margins) every single vote counts. please

column1: 305605;instagram;2018-10-09 00:37:33;FALSE;proud of the time #bretstephens of @nytimes retweet me.  my dear son
column2: sex is confusing.  take your time.  having sex- making love- is the essence of life.  without it
column4: your mother and i would not have had you
column6: our biggest blessings in life.  it's magic.  two people have the power to create life.  and like all magic
column8: it can destroy lives.  it's confusing.  even as i write you this letter that you will read in a few years
column10: wealthy and famous men are being put in jail for misusing this magic
column11: because they never learned this important lesson.  you know how when you walk into a apple store
column14: you want it all? that's how sex is.  you want everything that pleases your eyes and more.  but that's the thing.  toys are yours to have
column16: then throw away as you wish.  not women.  the person you have sex with must be someone you love
column17: someone who you want to make happy because their happiness matters even more than your own.  she's someone that not only pleases your eyes but warms your heart.  you talk. a lot.  and your souls connect
column18: and you realize that's the person you were meant to love.  sex is gentle.  sex is kind.  it's confusing.  because you'll be exposed to angry
column20: and you'll be taught to only look at women as body parts.  you'll be given the impression that you can change partners like used clothes.  but all that is the misuse of your magic.  loving sex is like a fire that warms you up on a cold night
column21: but when misused sex is like the fire that burns down the entire house.  so take your time.  go slow.  take time for romance.  take time for long kisses.  and chase her
column22: even if you're sure she is yours.  but
column23: never wish to posses or control her
column24: because if her happiness is truly important to you
column25: you will help her walk away when she wants to.  and when she decides to stay
column26: and wants you to love her
column27: that's the time for you to share your true magic. #himtoo #sex #metoo #newyorktimes #thenewyorktimes;;en;#bretstephens

column1: 305625;instagram;2018-10-09 00:02:19;FALSE;"i am sick of the media making white men look scary and women look weak.
men are not evil and women are not liars. we are none of those things. we are one. we are love.
i believe that sexual assault stems from the way in which our society views gender roles
column2: roles that are currently very much separate when in truth we are all extension from the same source.

column1: this imbalance separates and disconnects us from one another leaving us all misunderstood.
masculinity is traditionally seen as more “rough”
column2: associated with power and strength. while femininity is traditionally seen as more “soft”

column1: the contrast between the genders mirrors exactly what is happening when it comes to sexual assault
column2: with the men in the power seat and women playing a more submissive role.

column1: to make a change we need to start by re-defining these roles because we are no different and any separation that does exist has been societally created.
how can you blame a woman for wanting to wear skimpy clothing
column2: when that’s all she sees in the media?

column1: how can you blame a man for not wanting to surround himself with women scantily clothed when that’s all he sees in the media?
i am tired of society defining a woman’s worth based on how high her tits sit or how slim she is.
i am also tired of society defining a man’s worth based on how many women he sleeps with or how much money he has in his bank account.
it is one of the reasons why men feel more inclined to chase women around and why women appear more enticing to men.
and even if a woman says no
column2: it is met with conflict when the man is trying to validate his masculinity through his ability to have sex with her.

column1: a woman is literally set up for failure by a society that objectifies her.
it is not okay to sexualize
column3: and use a woman’s physical form to sell something.

column1: it is not okay to teach men to treat women as objects to be sold.
it is not okay to make women feel as though their value is based on how “sellable” they are.
it is not okay to condemn a man for crying.

it is not okay to shame a woman for speaking out. i thank dr ford for enduring so much. it will not be in vain. we must keep strong and get out and vote! your vote matters.  women’s rights matter.  we women can change things with our actions and create an impact by doing something.
dr. christine blasey ford did. “bravery is contagious. indeed

column1: 305696;instagram;2018-10-08 23:15:29;FALSE;"i have some stuff i’d like to say about the kavanaugh hearings and my own personal experiences. i don’t do facebook anymore
column2: and while i do have a blog
column3: my social medium these days is pretty much exclusively instagram.

column1: i want to try something new working with the instagram medium. it might be a little awkward
column2: but i’m gonna try this out and see what happens. this will be posted in 6 parts. i’m not holding back the posts
column3: but it may take a few for me to get all 6 up.

column1: i’m interested to hear feedback on this kind of post
column2: as well as feedback on what i have to say.

column1: most of the posts are just slides with words
column2: but since captions often go overlooked here
column3: i thought this would be an interesting experiment. and since i’ve got a bunch to say at this moment
column4: this seemed like a good time to try it out.

column1: part 1 of 6 [text in pic 1] we now interrupt your regularly scheduled @d_nelle programming for something uncomfortable. [text in pic 2] i’ve been doing my best to be gentle with myself as this kavanaugh storm blew in. i’ve focused on looking at cute puppy videos and adventures that friends are having. 🗣shout out to leo
column2: who was at work with his mom and dad last week and sporting a t-shirt that c and i made for his 1st birthday. 💯 would stare at photos of him all day.
who rode a broom through target yesterday.

who’s been going to gymnastics and now she and i share a love of the foam pit. [text in pic 3] i’ve tried to only read about the events in the senate when i can focus on and consider what i’m reading with a reasonable
column3: open-minded attitude. i’m lucky that i have a partner who is obsessively keeping up with things who i can ask to cliffs-notes things when i need it. [text in pics 4-9 in the comments]

column2: i know how deep and common the shame
column4: and powerlessness felt from sexual victimization is. the #metoo movement has brought a lot of relief and healing
column5: we've been able to connect and unite in our painful stories as well as take a huge burden of shame off. we can see our repression and abuse as a whole now which is huge. but it’s far from enough
column6: we're still so far as last week showed us. i want to use our collective horror and rage at seeing the pervasive sexual violence and society’s current protection of it to fuel change. i support @rainn
column7: an amazing organization that provides support services to rape
column9: and incest survivors as well as provides public education about sexual violence and advocates to improve public policy. i also think we need to show our men and boys a different way and @acalltomen does great work to show them how to embrace a healthy

column1: 305744;instagram;2018-10-08 23:03:17;FALSE;"to hold your hand means so much to me. .

there was a time i couldn’t be touched. i would have panic attacks. i was dealing with the worst of my ptsd and in therapy hoping to one day be able to accept or give a hug without fear pulsating through my body. .
sexual abuse recovery is different for each survivor so i can’t tell you how it will be
column3: but please know you can heal to a point you that you feel better than you did before recovery . .

column1: joining together with these strong women has made me even stronger. several years after my recovery
column2: i still know i can heal in many more ways. having their support is empowering and inspiring. .

column1: sharing even just the words #metoo can be a start. if you feel comfortable to share

column2: when i was raped (the second time) i reported it early the very next morning. the two police officers interrogated me and i answered all of the questions. yes
column4: his wife was the one to invite me over. yes
column5: his wife was sleeping in the next room over. no i wasn’t wearing underwear (which they asked me twice with judgmental looks upon their faces). i provided the police with my clothing that had potential dna evidence on it
column6: which i never saw again. i went to the hospital alone waited in complete filth (not being able to shower) for hours. i had a rape kit done on me which provided evidence of not only dna but documented the swollenness my vaginal walls from the trauma. the second the male doctor touched me (he was a gentle and kind medical professional) i shook and broke down in tears. i was given a prescription that would counteract less dangerous stds which made me vomit 5 times in the hospital parking structure after i was released. i couldn’t even bear to stay in the place i called home that night because i was too afraid. my gf checked us into a hotel slightly out of spokane because i was terrified. i felt completely destroyed. i missed a weekend of work and shut myself in at my girlfriend’s parents for nearly a week. i didn’t talk to anyone really. after a week passed and i had gone back to work was when the real hell set in. i didn’t even know at the time how severe my ptsd was. i spent months in pure torture even after i sought help through counseling. i called to check in with my case a handful of times to leave messages because they never answered. the one detective called back one time and i made it clear that i wanted to press charges against my attacker. i’ve never heard anything since. this was 2 years ago. this man who had an overwhelming amount of evidence against him walks free today. free to do and be who he wants with zero repercussions.

column1: so why don’t you tell me why i reported?
are you still wondering why women don’t report? because the system is set up to fail survivors. period.

column6: which i never saw again. i went to the hospital alone waited in complete filth (not being able to shower) for hours. i had a rape kit done on me which provided evidence of not only dna but documented the swollenness my vaginal walls from the trauma. the second the male doctor touched me (he was a gentle and kind medical professional) i shook and broke down in tears. i was given a prescription that would counteract less dangerous stds which made me vomit 5 times in the hospital parking structure after i was released. i couldn’t even bear to stay in the place i called home that night because i was too afraid. my gf checked us into a hotel slightly out of spokane because i was terrified. i felt completely destroyed. i missed a weekend of work and shut myself in at my girlfriend’s parents for nearly a week. i didn’t talk to anyone really. after a week passed and i had gone back to work was when the real hell set in. i didn’t even know at the time how severe my ptsd was. i spent months in pure toure even after i sought help through counseling. i called to check in with my case a handful of times to leave messages because they never answered. the one detective called back one time and i made it clear that i wanted to press charges against my attacker. i’ve never heard anything since. this was 2 years ago. this man who had an overwhelming amount of evidence against him walks free today. free to do and be who he wants with zero repercussions.

column1: my self esteem was non-existent. i was plagued by ptsd. and even missed the guy who abused me.⁣

and here i am today. older

column1: the us republicans have officially voted in brett kavanaugh as the ninth supreme court of the united states - so why is this such a momentous and repulsive moment? and why does it affect us all and not just americans?

column2: brett kavanaugh has been accused of multiple sexual assaults by credible
column3: law abiding women (although their credibility shouldn’t make them any more deserving of objectivity). let’s take a moment to look at the accusations against kavanaugh from a different angle: let’s pretend he’s been accused of attempted rape on a young
column6: instead of young white women. do you think the republican senate would so readily turn a blind eye to this man’s obvious lack of impartiality
column7: had he dared attack a man!? a straight one at that!! could they so easily cast aside these accusations as hearsay in this instance? or do you think they’d metaphorically lynch him? i think we all know the answer here.

column2: goes on and on about her love of beer
column3: has burst into fits of rage and tears in a federal hearing
column4: while muttering partisan propaganda. do we really think the republicans would back this crazy

column3: so that those who appear before them can have confidence that their cases will be decided fairly and in accordance with the law. brett kavanaugh has a complete lack of judicial restraint
column5: demonstrated by such comments as (about the democrats): “what goes around comes around”
column6: and his mollycoddling hyperpartisan rhetoric against ‘the left’ where he described his confirmation as “a calculated and orchestrated political hit

column1: 305849;instagram;2018-10-08 21:48:43;FALSE;"quite an interesting alignment of planets for this libra new moon. it's actually one of the more interesting ones i've seen in a while
column2: and so let's see if we can unpack some of it.~

column1: the libra new moon takes place right next to ceres. ceres is a dwarf planet in the asteroid belt that in 2006 was upgraded from asteroid to dwarf planet.~

column2: pluto was downgraded from planet to dwarf planet
column3: thus giving them the same status
column4: astronomically speaking. and at this libra new moon
column5: ceres and pluto are facing off in a conflictual square aspect.~

column1: what's fascinating is that these two characters in mythology have stories that are intimately interwoven. ceres is the goddess of harvest and abundance
column3: mother figure. ceres had a daughter
column4: persephone who was abducted into the underworld by pluto. this caused ceres tremendous grief and she was no longer able to look after the humans' agricultural affairs

column1: pluto eventually agreed to release persephone because he knew that eternal winter would destroy all life on the planet. but before doing so he tricked her into eating six pomegranate seeds.  and having eaten food from the underworld
column2: she became a part of that world and was obliged to return for three months every year.~

column1: and what's key here: that she agreed to return willingly to the underworld on a regular basis~

and we can see here the dynamic between ceres and pluto on center stage as they square off in the sky. we can also perhaps see the need to resolve the way that these energies play out in our lives and the world.~
one of the things that i see playing out very strongly is the need to balance these apparently opposing energies. ~

column2: we can understand what happens when we don’t go to the underworld to do our shadow work willingly: we’re dragged there.  and from a personal standpoint we’re invited to learn the necessity of stepping into that shadow work
column3: lest we be dragged there in a far more painful manner.  and as recent events show
column4: we may be dragged there in front of all our friends
column5: maybe on all the news stations and social media
column6: maybe in front of congress.";;en;;;;;;0;;robpaulastro;Rob Tim Paul;;0;False;3;0;0;17;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/b1dc126a2c6d41ee941bf8fcfa73940f/5D038ADF/t51.2885-15/e35/43163249_1956595707720065_3247997854320288889_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;"quite an interesting alignment of planets for this libra new moon. it is actually one of the more interesting ones i have seen in a while

column2: cause i never spoke openly about it. i was raped in college. i didnt want to speak or report the incident i jus wanted to take a shower. my best friend forced me to report the rape. the cops were mean to me. the lady kept asking why didnt i leave why didnt i call the cops. i felt like she was blaming me. i did not press charges the cop made me feel like it was my fault. even though i said no and was literally fighting this guy. yes i was throwing jabs. like frfr he dragged me on the floor by ankles when i would try to break free. i was in an ambulance i reported my rape at journal sq. for months i was tramatized by the sounds of sirens. i was afraid to go to school. i eventually transferred.  i didnt feel right speaking on this without saying i too was a victim of rape and i kno it is hard to come out.  #culture #billcosby #remyma #joe #women #empowerment #protect #rape #vitcimblaming #metoo #hiphop";;en;#SOTC

column1: i decided to share a picture about one of the times i felt the  most valuable.. my graduation with a gold rose......because i know now it’s scary time...
especially for many women. and many girls (and even men and even boys who’s been there)
regardless of whatever side you believe...it’s important to recognize that at this very moment many people feel uncared for and feel afraid.
but despite the decision that was made
column2: i just want to say to don’t be afraid.

column1: this isn’t about about a insensitive “women are doing great” comments or insensitive snl jokes. it isn’t about being funny or controversial. it’s about being strong. .it is about knowing that whoever you are. your voice matters. your body is made of precious stones. you are valuable. you’re life is precious. you have a destiny! you are here for a reason. don’t be afraid. whoever you are. god made you with a purpose! i’m praying for you. i’m praying for us.. to listen to each other..to truly love eachother...and for you whoever you are..to not be afraid. .

column1: 305938;instagram;2018-10-08 19:53:46;FALSE;"trigger warning: reference to assault�. the last few weeks have been a nonstop avalanche of triggers and trauma. this is a lot to hold - it’s a lot to witness
column2: and it’s a lot to contend with. i keep coming back to the invisibility of it all. the act of assault renders one invisible and that harm is reactivated by a culture that insists on not seeing any of this. a culture that embraces erasing
column4: and denying the pervasiveness of it all. we are looking for respite while swimming in this toxicity. it is everywhere and all at once.

column1: we’d be naive to suggest that this particular instance provides any more insight than the countless circumstances and examples that come before it. this was foretold. the ambivalence and disregard for our well being
column3: and our wholeness is well accounted for. they’ve done as they’ve been taught to do: whatever they must
column4: to keep us invisible. seeing us would mean seeing themselves and to see themselves would require a tremendous amount of courage and vulnerability. why bother when they can just pretend as if we aren’t here and as if we aren’t hurting. why bother when their inhumanity is the status quo.

column2: in the shadow of how hopeless it may seem
column3: my prayer remains simple and centered on us: may this bring us more clarity; may that clarity ignite our courage; may that courage awaken our power.

column1: i’m holding space for the rest of myself to catch up with my rage. i’m holding space for my grief and my trauma. and i’m holding space for the part of me that knows that something exists beyond this. the part of me that knows that our hearts are aligned with life itself and that a cosmos full of love and magic stands ready right beneath our wings. seeing us clearly. loving us fully. urging us on.
i believe that we are the alchemists.
i believe that this will end with us.

column1: 305943;instagram;2018-10-08 20:34:47;FALSE;"i wonder if an animal experiences disbelief and outrage like we feel when her very basic rights (of safety
column3: and respect) are completely ignored.  i wonder if she’s stunned and dejected when she looks for help and doesn’t get it.  i wonder if her heart goes numb for want of a witness.  does she feel invisible?  i wonder if she mourns her sweet and fierce life force that never had a chance to breathe.  i wonder if the person who cuts her down
column4: ends her hope… does his soul decay?  do we decay right along with it when we look away?

column1: 305944;instagram;2018-10-08 20:35:23;FALSE;"jamen låt oss stanna upp och backa några steg. just nu handlar det ju
column3: mycket om stackars män som (äntligen) fått några slags konsekvenser för sina griserier. #metoo - ett år senare - ”andra sidan kommer till tals”. men detta
column5: hatandet och tystandet gentemot tjejer och kvinnor som berättar om övergrepp har ju pågått något längre än sedan metoo-hösten 2017. detta👆var min vardag redan 2012. mina kollegor
column7: satt en våning ner på dåvarande jobbet och startade trådar i olika ”hemliga mejlinglistor” om att jag var (håll i hatten av förvåning) ”galen mytoman”. och som givetvis skyddades av våra manliga chefer. idag hade jag ställt till ett helvete. för inget ”drömjobb” är värt att ha om man blir behandlad såhär. men då var jag rädd. inte så konstigt. dom var 15-20 år äldre
column9: höll ihop. i stort sett ingen på jobbet backade mig
column10: i alla fall inte öppet. på julfesten försökte en manlig kollega kyssa mig och när jag puttade bort honom skrek han ”just det
column11: du polisanmäler väl alla killar som bara närmar sig!”. ingen backade mig. jag blev sjukskriven och hamnade i en depression. allt i sin ordning. den galna häxan hade fallit. patriarkatet skålade vidare. 🧛‍♂️

column1: detta är inget nytt som uppkommit i och med #metoo utan kvinnor har blivit misstrodda
column3: hatade och hotade på jobbet (och i typ alla andra sammanhang man kan tänka sig) sedan urminnes. det kan räcka med att bara inte finna sig i att bli kallad hora. det som hänt mig
column4: som händer mig är allt annat än unikt. det sker varje dag
column6: konstant. häxor och horor som ska brännas. knäckas och tystas. bara för att man vägrar rätta sig efter spelregler ingen människa ska behöva underkasta sig.

column1: mina gamla kollegor jobbar kvar. jag slutade. stod inte ut på en av alla arbetsplatser förpestad av sexism
column3: kvinnosyn från 50-talet. det är inte värt det. du är värd så mycket mer. din passion och ambition hör hemma någon annanstans. i en värld där det till exempel jag behövt uppleva i över ett decennium inte existerar. min berättelse är allt annat än unik. den speglar bara en värld där kvinnor inte har ett rimligt människovärde.";;en;#metoo

column1: 305948;instagram;2018-10-08 20:36:50;FALSE;"by myself ⚜️ no matter how much support you get as a survivor there are times when you just can’t explain how you feel... maybe you feel like the details of your trauma are so “ugh” 😖😠 that you feel bad sharing with even your best friend. or maybe you’ve shared so much that you feel like omg i need to stop talking. so you isolate. you spend time alone. and then it’s like .... “now what?” or “where do i go from here?” ✨👑 you’re not alone in that feeling
column2: and no matter what you have been through
column3: i 💯 guarantee you that your closest friends want to be there for you. keep taking steps toward healing and don’t be afraid to keep leaning on your support system. they are there for you!!

column1: you can also call a hotline and unload... but you are not crazy
column2: and you are definitely not alone. :

column1: 305969;instagram;2018-10-08 20:45:00;FALSE;i’ve come to realize a few things this weekend...reflecting on it today. have you ever been so stressed you treated those closest to you in a way you never would have and regretted it? i have. another example is my dads death...suicide. he didn’t do it to hurt anyone! he regrets it for he would never treat anyone badly in his right mind! he was so overwhelmed and sad with the way this world had been treating him and others. he said to me while i was pregnant “jessie

column3: it’s so bad now a days” i never wanted to believe that

column6: and when i am suicidal marijuana is my goto but i won’t actually ever commit i have children
column7: i’d never do it because of how it effected me as a child who watched her parents deteriorate. i have days where i’m very sad but i will always thrive to be better than that) i haven’t posted anything real in a while and i feel vulnerable doing so but the overload of posts about the sexual assault in the political aspect got me thinking too. here’s my #metoo

column9: maybe they watched there mother doing crooked things and they psychologically got fucked up they and made a mistake. think about this: the person was so stressed and overwhelmed
column10: no one around them gave them positive attention or even just a hug or a ear to listen...(now if the person doesn’t regret this action then yeah fuck that sick psycho
column11: cus they’ll never get better) but if they are a first offender we should help and care for the victims and perpetrators. we are in a world where being attractive or “sexy” is so important to all people...what do you do with being sexy besides being wanted

column1: 305974;instagram;2018-10-08 18:38:26;FALSE;"today begins the ""endangered bodies: genders and genres of insecurity"" conference at the university of lisbon. it is a great honour to have my artworks in the art exhibition surrounding the conference and to be able to participate at the artist round table taking place tomorrow.
the conference presentation managed to put into words what i've been struggling to formulate for years:

this line of research explores how gender and genre intersect in the creation of new narratives of insecurity but also observes how self-conscious approaches to genre by artists and writers have contributed to interrogate and critique notions of security and safety by highlighting how secure and safe spaces are often seen to be restricted to a specific “genus” or selected “genera
column2: ” reinforcing social categories and hierarchical classifications.

column2: cause i never spoke openly about it. i was raped in college. i didnt want to speak or report the incident i jus wanted to take a shower. my best friend forced me to report the rape. the cops were mean to me. the lady kept asking why didnt i leave why didnt i call the cops. i felt like she was blaming me. i did not press charges the cop made me feel like it was my fault. even though i said no and was literally fighting this guy. yes i was throwing jabs. like frfr he dragged me on the floor by ankles when i would try to break free. i was in an ambulance i reported my rape at journal sq. for months i was tramatized by the sounds of sirens. i was afraid to go to school. i eventually transferred.  i didnt feel right speaking on this without saying i too was a victim of rape and i kno it is hard to come out.  #culture #billcosby #remyma #joe #women #empowerment #protect #rape #vitcimblaming #metoo #hiphop
